          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Probability of Answering Next Question Correctly",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "574 Algebra learners, 4151 ASSISTments2009 learners, 1709 ASSISTments2017 learners",
          "ASSISTments, LEarners",
          "Sequences of Answers, Problem Difficulty, LMS logs",
          "[Student Knowledge Embeddings]",
          "DKVMN, which are part of the state-of-the-art of KT at the time struggles is vulnerable to longer sequences.\n\nDKT achieves good performances, even with longer sequences but struggles with interpretation.\n\nBKT is the most interpretable KT model but its performance is relatively subpar in comparison with other options.",
          "The authors introduce an LSTM module after the formation of the KV matrices.\n\nMoreover, the outputs of the LSTM module are subsequently given to a Bayesian Module which allows for greater interpretability of the model.\n",
          "As any Key-Value Network, the model requires the building of 2 matrices: \n\nA Key-Matrix that associates questions and knowledge components - which is static\n\nA Value Matrix that suffers different sets of Erase-Write operations to model the student’s actually knowledge.\n",
          "BKT, DKT, DKT+, DKVMN, SKVMN, enKT, BCKVMN",
          "Holdout Method",
          "AST09\n{AUC: 0.8649 - BCKVMN}\n\nAST17\n{AUC: 0.7757 - BCKVMN}\n\nAlgebra2005\n{AUC: 0.9662 - BCKVMN}",
          "Authors propose new architecture and perform multipe experiments:\n\nAnalysis of effect of different parameters (d, N, lambdas)\n\nThey also tested effects of changing the size of the training data\n\nClustering of exercises.\n\nA very preliminary start at using this approach for recomendations of in-session learning paths.",
          "Requires integration in order to be used for elarning apth recommendation. \n\nNo Cross-Validation."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
